Technology Brief -- Compaq Computer Corp.:
   Firm Announces Price Cuts
   On Some PCs, File Servers
The price cuts, aimed at making Compaq more competitive
with lower cost clone-makers, mean that a Compaq desktop
personal computer based on an Intel Corp.'s 80386
microprocessor can be purchased for less than $1,100; that a
80486sx-based PC will cost less than $2,500; and a
SystemPro/LT file server, which ties networks of PCs, will
cost less than $5,000.
   Compaq also said it plans to introduce today a "new
generation" of high-resolution monitors and video controllers
to provide sharper colors, faster speed and more realistic
images than earlier models.